n also be done in a CSS file using Tailwind CSS's `@apply` directive. Because the components render Hummingbird's CSS classes (such as `btn`), overriding the class changes every instance of the component."},"555":{"id":"/docs/customize/component-11","page_id":"/docs/customize/component","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/customize/component#using-css-variables","content":"Hummingbird components are styled with a set of CSS variables. These variables make it easy to customize styles either globally (across the entire project) or locally (for a specific component)."},"556":{"id":"/docs/customize/component-12","page_id":"/docs/customize/component","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/customize/component#using-css-variables","content":"For example, to update or customize the Button component, override its CSS variables:"},"557":{"id":"/docs/customize/component-13","page_id":"/docs/customize/component","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/customize/component#option-1-global-variables","content":"Override the theme variables globally under `@theme`. This will apply the changes across all components in the project."},"558":{"id":"/docs/customize/component-14","page_id":"/docs/customize/component","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/customize/component#option-2-local-variables","content":"Override the component variables locally under the component's class or a custom class. This will apply the changes only to that specific component."},"559":{"id":"/docs/customize/component-15","page_id":"/docs/customize/component","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/customize/component#option-2-local-variables","content":"To scope the change to only some buttons, pass a custom class through the `className` prop and target that class in CSS."},"560":{"id":"/docs/customize/dark-mode","page_id":"/docs/customize/dark-mode","type":"page","content":"Dark Mode","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Customize"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/customize/dark-mode"},"561":{"id":"/docs/customize/dark-mode-0","page_id":